  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat, then once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1687517621393-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1687517621393-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1687517621393-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1687517621393-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1687517621393-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and 300ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [450ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>with your <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>,<strong> half</strong> your <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>– this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1687517625321-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1687517625321-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1687517625321-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1687517625321-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1687517625321-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add your <strong>spaghetti</strong> with your <strong>dried oregano</strong>,<strong> chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Tip: You may need to break the spaghetti in half to fit the pan</p><p>Add a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1687517629022-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1687517629022-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1687517629022-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1687517629022-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1687517629022-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, increase the heat to medium-high and add a splash of the <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Cook for 4-5 min or until starting to char, turning the <strong>spaghetti</strong> occasionally</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1687517633943-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1687517633943-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1687517633943-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1687517633943-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1687517633943-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>cherry tomatoes </strong>to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a small pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 8-10 min or until starting to blister and char – these are your <strong>roast cherry tomatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1687517638072-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1687517638072-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1687517638072-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1687517638072-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1687517638072-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the spaghetti is slightly charred, add the <strong>tomato stock</strong> a ladle at a time, stirring occasionally for 7-8 min or until all of the stock is absorbed and the pasta is cooked with a slight bite – this is your <strong>assassin's spaghetti</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash more water if it is looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1687517643193-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1687517643193-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1687517643193-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1687517643193-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1687517643193-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>remaining balsamic vinegar</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>in a large bowl with 1 tsp [1 1/2 tsp] <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>– this is your<strong> balsamic dressing</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>black olives</strong> in half</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped olives</strong> and <strong>salad</strong> to the bowl and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>balsamic & olive salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1687517648968-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1687517648968-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1687517648968-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1687517648968-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1687517648968-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>assassin's spaghetti </strong>and sprinkle over your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Top with the<strong> roast cherry tomatoes</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>balsamic & olive salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
